{"id": "EUVD-2022-55868", "enisaUuid": "ede7f04b-20fd-3f9c-8c4f-60b00181a29c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nauxdisplay: hd44780: Fix potential memory leak in hd44780_remove()\n\nhd44780_probe() allocates a memory chunk for hd with kzalloc() and\nmakes \"lcd->drvdata->hd44780\" point to it. When we call hd44780_remove(),\nwe should release all relevant memory and resource. But \"lcd->drvdata\n->hd44780\" is not released, which will lead to a memory leak.\n\nWe should release the \"lcd->drvdata->hd44780\" in hd44780_remove() to fix\nthe memory leak bug.", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T15:30:27", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-30T15:30:27", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8311961a1724bfc64390c539dedc31e067a80315", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6cd37f8232f5e169a723e1d5fbe3b2139c2ef763", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5d407911e605702ffcc0e97a6db546592ab27dd0", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ddf75a86aba2cfb7ec4497e8692b60c8c8fe0ee7", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50830"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50830"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "22e59665-af91-3d13-bddb-817e0e4d3768", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.18"}, {"id": "3fa5643b-8715-3b7a-a36b-a92b8e44f1fe", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "718e05ed92ecac0d9d3954bcc8064527c3ce7565 <8311961a1724bfc64390c539dedc31e067a80315"}, {"id": "57667424-b44a-326d-8f03-f929aae81c56", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.11"}, {"id": "8548545f-d3d0-365e-b7c1-8c67eead142b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "718e05ed92ecac0d9d3954bcc8064527c3ce7565 <5d407911e605702ffcc0e97a6db546592ab27dd0"}, {"id": "8ed03c5f-be12-390a-88b4-6dea38cce534", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.100"}, {"id": "ab5ddeba-eca8-3a5a-ac0f-9412fe5d12c1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "ab728054-23c